</dd>
</dl>

<p id="_c5116a11-6c41-d219-9b14-fc82c545d1aa">with a relative standard uncertainty of <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mn>4</mn>
    <mo>×</mo>
    <msup>
      <mn>10</mn>
      <mrow>
        <mi>−</mi>
        <mn>10</mn>
      </mrow>
    </msup>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>4 xx 10^(−10)</asciimath></stem> apply to the radiation of a dye laser (or frequency-doubled He-Ne laser) stabilized with an iodine cell, within or external to the laser, having a cold-finger temperature of <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mn>6</mn>
      <mo>±</mo>
      <mn>2</mn>
      <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo rspace="thickmathspace">⁢</mo>
    <mrow xref="U_NISTu23">
      <mstyle mathvariant="normal">
        <mi>°C</mi>
      </mstyle>
      
      
    </mrow>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>(6 +- 2) "unitsml(degC)"</asciimath></stem><fn id="_591cc152-926d-9723-2057-93c8b05ed722" reference="2"><p id="_8f61a076-4e71-0b50-658d-405b5917587a">For the specification of operating conditions, such as temperature, modulation width and laser power, the symbols ± refer to a tolerance, not an uncertainty.</p>
</fn>.</p>
</clause>

